I also have this scrubber
which will allow me to zap to

00:07:04.700 --> 00:07:06.360
a far location in the book.

00:07:06.370 --> 00:07:09.900
This is a fairly short book,
so I don't really need that.

00:07:10.110 --> 00:07:15.030
And when I land on a given chapter,
we have here a list of the

00:07:15.180 --> 00:07:18.730
sections within that chapter that
function as a set of hyperlinks.

00:07:18.740 --> 00:07:22.230
I can tap on one and be brought
to that location in the book.

00:07:23.320 --> 00:07:26.400
So this is the second page
we've seen in this book.

00:07:26.490 --> 00:07:29.500
You look at this,
and it should feel like a real book,

00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:29.900
right?

00:07:30.230 --> 00:07:31.980
There's real graphic
design happening here.

00:07:32.020 --> 00:07:34.330
There's control over the
typographic elements.

00:07:34.400 --> 00:07:41.850
There is imagery,
and it overall feels like not something

00:07:42.240 --> 00:07:42.910
that -- it feels like something that you
