but we will put him back because
we have much to cover today.

00:09:00.460 --> 00:09:01.750
Although he's got some
smart stuff to say.

00:09:03.110 --> 00:09:05.000
Next up we have the gallery.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:08.990
And in the gallery you can see
one of the tenets of the design,

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:11.590
which was that things should
be interactive on the page,

00:09:11.730 --> 00:09:13.360
and they should be
interactive in full screen.

00:09:13.610 --> 00:09:16.600
Each of those experiences should
offer something different,

00:09:16.600 --> 00:09:20.500
but you shouldn't have to kind of switch
modes too heavily between the two.

00:09:20.630 --> 00:09:22.800
So here I can browse that gallery.

00:09:22.810 --> 00:09:25.890
If there's something
that piques my interest,

00:09:25.890 --> 00:09:29.490
I can bring it to full screen and
continue to swipe through the images.

00:09:29.490 --> 00:09:29.490
And again, pinch when I'm done.

00:09:31.310 --> 00:09:33.250
Next up we have the Keynote widget.

00:09:33.560 --> 00:09:37.040
I work within the iWork team,
and we thought as the developers of

00:09:37.040 --> 00:09:41.600
Keynote that it would make an excellent
tool for creating animated diagrams.

00:09:41.690 --> 00:09:45.190
So here I have an example of
stem cell differentiation,

00:09:45.190 --> 00:09:50.260
which is just a deck of slides
that are being animated using

00:09:50.260 --> 00:09:52.950
a simple magic move transition.

00:09:54.540 --> 00:09:56.270
So you can see here that just
through the use of Keynote,

00:09:56.330 --> 00:09:59.780
you can create kind of rich
interactive experiences without

00:09:59.780 --> 00:10:01.660
any code being required.

00:10:09.070 --> 00:10:11.340
On to the next section.

00:10:11.380 --> 00:10:12.820
And here is a 3D widget.

00:10:12.950 --> 00:10:13.790
Why?

00:10:13.920 --> 00:10:16.230
Because it's very cool.

00:10:16.780 --> 00:10:18.340
So I can interact with
this thing on the page,

00:10:18.340 --> 00:10:21.240
or as you guessed it,
bring it to full screen and

00:10:21.240 --> 00:10:23.300
look at it in all its glory.

00:10:23.300 --> 00:10:26.220
I like to stare death
straight in the eye.

00:10:28.560 --> 00:10:32.400
