double tap to reset the view.

00:10:32.760 --> 00:10:35.720
Next up is the interactive image,
which looks like a traditional

00:10:35.720 --> 00:10:38.530
annotated diagram that you might
find in any given textbook,

00:10:38.590 --> 00:10:40.400
but this is a lot more.

00:10:40.510 --> 00:10:42.840
Here I can tap on one of these
interactive callouts to reveal

00:10:42.840 --> 00:10:45.700
additional information about a
feature in the underlying image.

00:10:45.890 --> 00:10:49.310
And you'll notice that we kind
of zoomed the frame up to kind

00:10:49.310 --> 00:10:51.470
of put emphasis on that feature.

00:10:54.170 --> 00:10:55.340
Do you think I can go to full screen?

00:10:55.340 --> 00:10:58.100
You know I can.

00:10:58.230 --> 00:11:00.800
And when I'm in there,
I can continue to zoom around,

00:11:00.890 --> 00:11:05.170
tap on these things, tap to put it away,
and I'm done.

