So I pointed out that we
have kind of a rich layout.

00:12:52.900 --> 00:12:54.460
Typography is important to us.

00:12:54.540 --> 00:12:57.810
Graphic design is very important to us.

00:12:57.960 --> 00:12:59.300
And we thought that's
great for landscape,

00:12:59.300 --> 00:13:02.100
but what can we do in
portrait that makes sense?

00:13:02.110 --> 00:13:04.330
We didn't want the authors of the book,
the designers of the book,

00:13:04.330 --> 00:13:06.500
to have to lay out their book twice.

00:13:06.590 --> 00:13:10.610
So what we did is we decided
to derive a view for them.

00:13:10.760 --> 00:13:12.170
So as I changed the
orientation of my device,

00:13:12.220 --> 00:13:13.830
we go to the portrait flow mode.

00:13:14.020 --> 00:13:16.580
And here you probably guessed,
we've taken all the textual

00:13:16.580 --> 00:13:18.670
content from the book,
we've put it into this

00:13:18.670 --> 00:13:20.280
river of text at right,
and then we've taken

